DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(2,5,1);
$b = random(2,3,1);
$pi = 3.14159265359;
$V0 = 60*$b*$a;
$r0 = (3*$V0/(4*$pi))**(1/3);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

Helium is pumped into a spherical balloon at a rate of $a cubic
feet per second.  How fast is the radius increasing after $b
minutes?
$BR
Note: The volume of a sphere is given by \(V=(4/3)\pi r^3\).
$BR
$BR
Rate of change of radius (in feet per second) = \{ans_rule(20) \}
$BR

EOT

$ans = $a/(4*$pi*$r0**2);
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

ENDDOCUMENT();
